SIMPLE: martyr
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Martyr
<hw>Mar"tyr</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS., from L.
<ets>martyr</ets>, Gr. <grk>ma`rtyr</grk>, <grk>ma`rtys</grk>, prop., a
witness; cf. Skr. <ets>sm⟦rsdot⟧</ets> to remember, E.
<ets>memory</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>One who, by his death, bears witness to the truth of
the gospel; one who is put to death for his religion; <as>as,
<persfn>Stephen</persfn> was the first Christian
<ex>martyr</ex></as>.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To be a <qex>martyr</qex>, signifies only to witness the truth of
Christ; but the witnessing of the truth was then so generally attended
with persecution, that martyrdom now signifies not only to witness, but
to witness by death.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, one who sacrifices his life, his station, or
what is of great value to him, for the sake of principle, or to sustain
a cause.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Then if thou fall'st, O Cromwell,⟦br⟧
Thou fall'st a blessed <qex>martyr</qex> !</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Martyr</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Martyr
<hw>Mar"tyr</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Martyred</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Martyring</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To put to
death for adhering to some belief, esp. Christianity; to sacrifice on
account of faith or profession.</def> <rj><au>Bp. Pearson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To persecute; to torment; to torture.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The lovely Amoret, whose gentle heart⟦br⟧
Thou <qex>martyrest</qex> with sorrow and with smart.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Racked with sciatics, <qex>martyred</qex> with the stone.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Martyrdom</ent>⟦br⟧
